"1040":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-13","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box","content":"**Important**: Since `Flex` and `Grid` extend `Box`, prefer them for layouts. Use `Box` only when you need a non-flex, non-grid container."},"1041":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-14","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#props","content":"The `Box` component accepts the following props:"},"1042":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-15","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#scale-sizes","content":"The spacing props use semantic t-shirt sizes for padding, gap, and other spacing properties:"},"1043":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-16","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#scale-sizes","content":"`xs` - Extra small spacing"},"1044":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-17","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#scale-sizes","content":"`sm` - Small spacing"},"1045":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-18","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#scale-sizes","content":"`md` - Medium spacing"},"1046":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-19","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#scale-sizes","content":"`lg` - Large spacing"},"1047":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-20","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#scale-sizes","content":"`xl` - Extra large spacing"},"1048":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-21","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#scale-sizes","content":"`2xl` - 2x extra large spacing"},"1049":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-22","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#scale-sizes","content":"Custom CSS values are also supported for edge cases."},"1050":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-23","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#padding","content":"The padding props support t-shirt sizes and CSS logical properties for RTL support."},"1051":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-24","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#elevation","content":"The elevation prop adds visual depth using box-shadow."},"1052":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-25","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#rounding","content":"The rounding prop sets border-radius. Use `full` for fully rounded corners."},"1053":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-26","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#polymorphic-as-prop","content":"Box is fully polymorphic - the `as` prop allows rendering as any HTML element or custom component while preserving type-safe props."},"1054":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-27","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#polymorphic-as-prop","content":"**HTML Elements:** When using `as=\"button\"`, TypeScript enforces button-specific props like `type`, `disabled`, and `onClick`."},"1055":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-28","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#polymorphic-as-prop","content":"**Custom Components:** When using `as={MyComponent}`, Box accepts that component's props. If there's a prop name conflict, Box's props take priority."},"1056":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-29","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#polymorphic-as-prop","content":"**Typed Refs:** Refs are correctly typed based on the `as` value - `useRef<HTMLButtonElement>` works with `as=\"button\"`."},"1057":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-30","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#alignment","content":"Self-alignment props allow Box to position itself within flex or grid containers."},"1058":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-31","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#rtl-support","content":"Box uses CSS logical properties (`padding-inline-start`, `padding-block-end`, etc.) which automatically adapt to RTL layouts. No additional configuration is needed."},"1059":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/box-32","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/box","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/box#design-tokens","content":"All spacing, elevation, and rounding values are derived from the theme. If no theme is provided, default values are used. This ensures consistency across the design system."},"1060":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/grid","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/grid","type":"page","content":"Grid","breadcrumbs":["Docs","Components","Layout"],"tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/grid"},"1061":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/grid-0","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/grid","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/components/layout/grid","content":"Two-dimensional CSS Grid layout component for complex grid-based layouts with rows and columns"},"1062":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/grid-1","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/grid","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/grid#installation","content":"Installation"},"1063":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/grid-2","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/grid","type":"heading","tags":[],"url":"/docs/components/layout/grid#props","content":"Props"},"1064":{"id":"/docs/components/layout/grid-3","page_id":"/docs/components/layout/grid","type